{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"b37b04e8-da0a-4ce9-bb0e-453859aca908","content":"Good news — in .NET 10, `dotnet test` uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform **by default**. You no longer need `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport`; it's only required on .NET 9 and earlier SDKs. You can safely remove it.\n\n`EnableMSTestRunner` is still needed — it makes MSTest produce an executable test host.","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01E16rPRHF5voRHkhk6Tt2aL","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Removing obsolete property"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_013FoYMyGfQM8eGXD2hc55me","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-af84cc9173414658b413b2c5f28da4e6/TestProject.csproj","old_str":"    <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n    <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>","new_str":"    <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-af84cc9173414658b413b2c5f28da4e6/TestProject.csproj."}],"interactionId":"480fd80c-0a75-40fa-b593-cbbdd194cd48","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is on .NET 10 SDK and wants to know about native MTP support. Let me provide the key information:\n\nIn .NET 10, `dotnet test` natively supports Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP) without needing the `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property. Starting with .NET 10 SDK, MTP is the default test runner integration, so that property is no longer needed.\n\nThe key changes:\n1. `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` is no longer needed in .NET 10 — it's the default behavior.\n2. `EnableMSTestRunner` is still needed to produce an executable test host.\n\n\n3. If they want to revert to VSTest instead, they can explicitly disable MTP in their project file.","outputTokens":532,"requestId":"7C18:12D387:264F870:2A6D89D:69F9412F"},"id":"c78da5f1-2d5b-485e-b59e-e712ec60e68b","timestamp":"2026-05-05T01:00:40.669Z","parentId":"b3c73be6-d38d-40d7-890b-d6033b9d9073"}
